The paper discusses machine learning techniques and privacy issues related to data sharing, which are common topics in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes solutions for preserving privacy, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of distributed datasets and the need for efficient and accurate learning models suggest the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and techniques for data analysis, which is related to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses privacy concerns related to sensitive information, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
